blog.description:
The names Jacqueline. I go by Jackie or Dude because that's what Taylor Swift called me when I met her on June 1st, 2018 in Chicago, Illinois.
Taylor followed 8/15/15 and liked 1x a photo of me and my best friend just chilling and a photo of me and the love of my life on New Years day and I haven't recovered since. She also told me she saw my tour outfits and thought I was really dedicated so she saved them and had someone come find me so she could meet me!!!!!
 Feeling 23 and blessed, living in a big ol' (windy) city.

Taylor Swift enthusiast since 2008. Message me, let's be friends!

summary: 3 years ago today @taylorswift started following me on tumblr. Since then she has liked 3 of my own posts, a handful of things...
caption:
3 years ago today @taylorswift started following me on tumblr. Since then she has liked 3 of my own posts, a handful of things I’ve reblogged, screenshotted my tour outfit, and a little less then 3 months ago I finally was able to meet this amazing human being who does more than you can imagine.

Taylor,
I didnt say much when we met because i was so in shock and i know first impressions are a lot and i hope you dont forget me. I left a letter for you with Stephanie from TaylorNation with a rainbow of water colors spilling down from the top of the envelope with my name (Jackie) on it. I hope it got to you and you got to read all the things i didnt say. I hope you know how much meeting you meant to me and how you changed my life for the better. You are an amazing role model.

Its 5 a.m and I’m on my way to work, trying to find the words to describe how much you mean to me, but all that I can think of is I love you. And I do. I love you so so so much Taylor. Thank you for all that you have done. For me, for others, for everything. You have been a constant light in my life, like you have been for others, and I can never repay you for all the times you were there for me when I was alone on the bathroom floor. You and your music saved me in more ways than one and for that I’m grateful. Here’s to 3 years of knowing one another, a few months of meeting, and 10+ years of loving you unconditionally.
You will always be my hero.

Stay gold,
Jackie 💕
